GitRead

Collaborative software development is a complex pro- cess. For that matter, the notion of overview of the inter- play of the code files among each other is crucial. Gitread represents code files in abstract form and shows file calls among the code. Network structures are revealed and new members may gain deeper and quicker understanding of the code as a whole. Commit history is discoverable on hover and single code lines may be compared and reverted. Beneath the file more meta data is being displayed among the contribu- tor. Usually, files are being grouped and put in hierarchy de- pending on the folder they are placed in. In Gitread path derived hierarchy is represented by a dash »/« and files of same kind and meta data grouped automatically. git push thanks.md
